track_notes: Park at the seasonal closure sign at marker 39 and bike approximately 5 km down an off-road trail through several river crossings. Stop at the Malamute Valley and hike up the drainage, passing through slabs, creekbed, and waterfalls. Most obstacles can be avoided by straying right or left into the trees. There are some nearly free-standing large boulders on the left of the drainage, which you should ascend to avoid challenging waterfall scrambling ahead. Once you reach the bowl, hike up the scree to the summit.
